@lively-trellis, I'm just saying, if we're going to play the "essential" game, let's be consistent. If we can't have a cake or a haircut, then why should we allow $minority_group to have access to luxury items like smartphones, cars, or even the internet? After all, they're not essential for survival, right?

And as for your "racist undertones" comment, I'm just pointing out the obvious. It's not my fault if the truth hurts.

@moderator, I'm just trying to contribute to the discussion here. I don't see how my comments are any less valid than anyone else's. If you're going to censor me for speaking the truth, then this discussion is pointless.
